OL,3,CChild killer's parole hearing will not
OL,4,Cbe public following 'fresh allegations'
OL,6,FIn June last year, the Parole Board
OL,7,Ffound the decision to recall Pitchfork
OL,8,Fto prison was flawed and said his
OL,9,Fdetention was no longer necessary for
OL,10,Fpublic safety. But this ruling was
OL,11,Fblocked by then-justice secretary Alex
OL,12,FChalk as he called for the decision to
OL,13,Frelease Pitchfork to be reviewed.
OL,15,FAlthough Pitchfork lost his latest bid
OL,16,Ffor freedom in December, earlier this
OL,17,Fyear he successfully challenged the
OL,18,Fruling to keep him behind bars.
